The Data Quality component allows to perform quality and consistency checks on input data for the Document Legal Archive profile, and produce a detailed report containing any non-conformities identified during quality checks.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

This resource may be used in conjunction with the DataQuality operator that can be defined within the Mapper. For more information, see: [DT3 DataQuality Operator.](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-dataquality-operator)

## Configuring the Data Quality profile settings
The **Quality checks **section allows to enable and configure the required quality checks for the Doxee Legal Archive data quality profile.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

In particular, it is possible to enable the following checks:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Index Consistency**

The system checks the consistency of an index file in CSV format. For more information, see [Index Consistency checks](/doxee-platform/docs/dt3-data-quality-component#index-consistency-checks) below.

**File Size**

The system checks the size of the input file.

In the **Lower than **field, enter the numeric value of the threshold (in MB) for the check on the input file; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Consistency of Index File against PdV (check also timestamp if present)**

The system checks that the IDX file (the index) is consistent with the set of documents actually present in the package. If the documents are expected to be timestamped, then the check is run first against the document class on LEA, to make sure that the document class defined in the IDX matches the one in LEA and that it is set to have a timestamped input.

**Consistency of Offset File against PdV**

The system first checks that the document class has the offset flag activated. Next, it checks that the offset index and the IDX index are consistent.

**Consistency of Dossier File against PdV**

The system checks that the dossier file is consistent with the given PdV.

**Consistency of Receipts File against PdV**

The system checks that the receipt file is consistent with the given PdV. This check is required for applications related to the Public Administration.

**Legal Entity and Document Categories**

The system checks that the legal entities and document categories present in the IDX files actually exist in LEA.

**Document Category Metadata**

The system compares the metadata information retrieved from the LEA system with the type of data provided in the IDX file.

**Cause job error if DQ fails**

The system forces the DT task to fail if the data quality check fails.

### Index Consistency checks
The **Index Consistency **section allows to check the consistency of an index file in CSV format. In particular, it allows to check the presence of a given field in each column of the file.

- Expand the **Index consistency **menu. The configuration panel shows the available settings:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Enable the toggle corresponding to the **Index Field **that you want to check.

- Set the field parameters that you want to check for:

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Index Field**

Enter the name that you want to assign to the customizable index field.

**Data type**

Field type:

**String **

- **Number **

- **Date**

**Length**

Field length (number of characters)

**Nullable**

Select this option to check if the field in the index file is null.

> Note

The **Nullable **checkbox is deselected by default because the system, by default, verifies that the index file field is not null.

- Repeat steps 23 to check additional fields in the index file.

> Note

In addition to customizable fields, there are other predefined, non-custom fields for which the Data Quality component automatically performs quality checks.

The available predefined fields are:

**Legal Entity Code **

- **File name**

- **Document category code **

- **Source ID**

- **Source **

- **Sorting**

- **Document date **

- **Description **

- **Pages**

The Data Quality component checks that the fields listed are present in the index file of the PdV in predetermined positions, and that the date value is valid.

## Configuring the Data Quality report
The **Reporting **section allows to configure the type of data quality report that will be produced in output in the Preview phase.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Select the **Report type**; the available options are:

**Doxee**: a detailed report, predefined by Doxee (default)

- **UniSincro**: a detailed report defined according to the UNI 11386:2010 SInCRO (Supporting Interoperability in Preservation and Retrieval of Digital Objects) standard, provided by the Agency for Digital Italy (AgID)

- *(optional) *Upload an external XSLT file to perform format transformations and change the look of the detailed report file. This functionality is useful, for example, to change the view of the detailed report file to meet the specific needs of a customer.

> Note

To view the data quality report, it is necessary to build and preview the Data Transformation project. For more information, see: Managing DT3 Projects.

At the end of the pipeline execution, the Quality component automatically returns a detailed report file in XML format (default).
